This is caused by the following lines in `navPath.cpp`:

```
if(dtStatusFailed(mQuery->findNearestPoly(from, extents, &mFilter, &startRef, from)))
```

According to a comment in `DetourNavMeshQuery.cpp`, the call to `findNearestPoly` returns success if there are no polygons in the search area. Which seems like a Recast bug, but we can fix it on our end by manually checking `startRef` and `endRef`.

The relevant comment:

```
/// @note If the search box does not intersect any polygons the search will 
/// return #DT_SUCCESS, but @p nearestRef will be zero. So if in doubt, check 
/// @p nearestRef before using @p nearestPt.
```
